{"dist-tags":{"alpha":"1.0.7-alpha.0","beta":"1.0.7-beta.0","latest":"1.0.8"},"license":"MIT","users":{},"description":"[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/timer.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/timer) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/timer)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/timer)","name":"@byted-service/timer","author":"","readme":"# @byted-service/timer\n\n[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/timer.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/timer) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/timer)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/timer)\n\n[简体中文](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/timer/README.md) | [English](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/timer/README.en.md) | [CHANGELOG](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/timer/CHANGELOG.md)\n\nUsed for various asynchronous operation timing and timeout calculation.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/timer --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## Quick start\n\n```ts\nimport { promisify } from 'util';\n\nimport { Timer } from '@byted-service/timer';\n\nconst sleep = promisify(setTimeout);\n\n(async () => {\n    const timer = new Timer(1000);\n\n    await sleep(10);\n\n    console.log(\n        'AsyncOperation took %d ms, and %d ms left.',\n        timer.cost(),\n        timer.remain()\n    );\n    console.log(\n        'AsyncOperation took %d μs, and %d μs left.',\n        timer.cost('μs'),\n        timer.remain('μs')\n    );\n    console.log(\n        'AsyncOperation took %d ns, and %d ns left.',\n        timer.cost('ns'),\n        timer.remain('ns')\n    );\n})();\n```\n\nUse `timer.call()` to retry asynchronous operations.\n\n```ts\nimport { promisify } from 'util';\n\nimport { Timer } from '@byted-service/timer';\n\nconst sleep = promisify(setTimeout);\n\n(async () => {\n    const timer = new Timer(1000);\n\n    const result = await timer.call(\n        async (timeout, i) => {\n            console.log(\n                'Try asyncOperation with %d ms, %d times',\n                timeout,\n                i + 1\n            );\n\n            await sleep(timeout);\n\n            if (i < 2) {\n                throw new Error('Try later');\n            }\n\n            return 'async result';\n        },\n        { fnTimeout: 10, times: 3 }\n    );\n\n    console.log('Got result from asyncOperation: \"%s\"', result);\n\n    try {\n        await timer.call(\n            async (timeout, i) => {\n                console.log(\n                    'Try asyncOperation with %d ms, %d times',\n                    timeout,\n                    i + 1\n                );\n\n                await sleep(timeout);\n\n                throw new Error('Try later');\n            },\n            {\n                fnTimeout: 10,\n                times: 3,\n                finalError: (err) =>\n                    new Error(`Finally got error \"${err.message}\"`),\n            }\n        );\n    } catch (err) {\n        console.log('Got error: %s', err);\n    }\n})();\n```\n\nUse `timer.child()` to get multiple `timers` for timing separately.\n\n```ts\nimport { promisify } from 'util';\n\nimport { Timer } from '@byted-service/timer';\n\nconst sleep = promisify(setTimeout);\n\n(async () => {\n    const timer = new Timer(1000);\n\n    const readTimer = timer.child();\n    await sleep(10);\n    console.log('Read operation took %d ms', readTimer.cost());\n\n    const writeTimer = timer.child();\n    await sleep(10);\n    console.log('Write operation took %d ms', writeTimer.cost());\n\n    console.log('All operations took %d ms', timer.cost());\n})();\n```\n\nUse `timer.timeline()` to record the time spent on each asynchronous operation.\n\n```ts\nimport { promisify } from 'util';\n\nimport { Timer } from '@byted-service/timer';\n\nconst sleep = promisify(setTimeout);\n\n(async () => {\n    const timer = new Timer(1000);\n\n    const middlewares = new Array(10)\n        .fill('')\n        .map((_, i) => ({ name: `middleware${i}`, fn: () => sleep(i) }));\n\n    for (const middleware of middlewares) {\n        timer.timeline(middleware.name);\n        await middleware.fn();\n        timer.timeline(middleware.name);\n    }\n\n    console.log('All middlewares took %O', timer.timelines());\n})();\n```\n\n## API\n\n### new Timer([options])\n\nCreate timer.\n\n-   options: When it is `number | null`, it is equivalent to `options.timeout`.\n    -   unit: Time unit, the default value is `ms`\n    -   timeout: Timeout, the default value is `null` ( Infinity )\n    -   startOnCreate: Whether to automatically call `timer.start()` upon creation, the default value is `true`\n\n### timer.unit\n\nTimer unit.\n\n### timer.timeout\n\nTimer timeout.\n\n### timer.start()\n\nStart timer, it can be used with `options.startOnCreate` for the case of `time to create timer != time to start timer`.\n\n### timer.stop([unit])\n\nStop timer, the internal state of the timer will stop changing after the call.\n\n-   `timer.cost()`、`timer.remain()` will return a fixed value.\n-   `timer.call()`、`timer.child()`、`timer.timeline()` will throw.\n\n### timer.cost([unit])\n\nQuery timer cost time.\n\n-   unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit).\n\n### timer.remain([unit[, timeout]])\n\nQuery timer remain time.\n\n-   unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit).\n-   timeout: Timeout, the default value is [timer.timeout](#timertimeout).\n\nPS: If it is infinite, it will return `Infinity`.\n\n### timer.call(fn[, options])\n\nTry to call the function within the time limit.\n\n-   fn: Call function.\n-   options.times: The number of attempts, the default value is 1.\n-   options.fnTimeout: The maximum timeout time for each call, the default value is [timer.remain()](#timerremainunit-timeout).\n-   options.unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit)\n-   options.finalError: The final error of the call failure, the function return value will be thrown when it is a function, otherwise the value will be thrown directly.\n\nPS: If the time is infinite, the first parameter of `fn` will be `undefined`.\n\n### timer.child([options])\n\nGet child timer.\n\n-   options: See [new Timer()](#new-timeroptions).\n\n### timer.hasTimeline(key)\n\nIs there a timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n\n### timer.delTimeline(key)\n\nDelete a timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n\n### timer.timeline(key[, unit])\n\nStart or stop timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n-   unit: Time unit.\n\nPS: Second call means stop.\n\n### timer.timelines([unit])\n\n-   unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit)\n-   Returns: Timeline array.\n    -   key: Timeline key.\n    -   cost: Timeline cost.\n    -   unit: Time unit.\n    -   stoped: Whether the timeline is stopped.\n","time":{"1.0.4-alpha.0":"2021-09-24T10:26:00.161Z","1.0.7-beta.0":"2022-06-23T10:08:06.520Z","modified":"2024-07-26T03:56:31.694Z","1.0.3":"2021-09-16T08:29:14.135Z","1.0.5":"2021-12-29T10:49:49.288Z","1.0.7-alpha.0":"2022-06-23T09:58:35.280Z","1.0.5-alpha.0":"2021-12-27T03:11:26.902Z","1.0.7":"2022-06-24T03:53:17.488Z","created":"2021-03-28T07:42:23.291Z","1.0.4":"2021-09-24T10:32:23.658Z","1.0.6":"2022-06-08T10:11:32.856Z","1.0.8":"2024-07-26T03:56:31.694Z","1.0.0":"2021-03-28T07:42:23.291Z","1.0.1":"2021-05-27T09:59:47.654Z","1.0.2":"2021-05-31T02:53:41.103Z"},"versions":{"1.0.7":{"types":"lib/index.d.ts","_npmVersion":"lerna/undefined/node@v14.19.3+x64 (linux)","dependencies":{"tslib":"^1.9.3"},"dist":{"size":6754,"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/timer/-/timer-1.0.7.tgz","unpackedSize":27966,"fileCount":15,"integrity":"sha512-bBiy4FAw+L+EwfpY5NyQH5W9jYlr+t76WhbtYC1TmYLjQlWjnwPnVAf3JW+e/be+VE6+8W/AoXlY6DQHIpNanQ==","shasum":"9c050f