y`.\n\n### timer.call(fn[, options])\n\nTry to call the function within the time limit.\n\n-   fn: Call function.\n-   options.times: The number of attempts, the default value is 1.\n-   options.fnTimeout: The maximum timeout time for each call, the default value is [timer.remain()](#timerremainunit-timeout).\n-   options.unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit)\n-   options.finalError: The final error of the call failure, the function return value will be thrown when it is a function, otherwise the value will be thrown directly.\n\nPS: If the time is infinite, the first parameter of `fn` will be `undefined`.\n\n### timer.child([options])\n\nGet child timer.\n\n-   options: See [createTimer()](#createtimeroptions).\n\nPS: By default, when the parent timer is recycled, the child timer will also be recycled. You can call `timer.unref()` to release the relationship.\n\n### timer.unref()\n\nReleasing the timer relationship.\n\n### timer.hasTimeline(key)\n\nIs there a timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n\n### timer.delTimeline(key)\n\nDelete a timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n\n### timer.timeline(key[, unit])\n\nStart or stop timeline.\n\n-   key: Timeline key.\n-   unit: Time unit.\n\nPS: Second call means stop.\n\n### timer.timelines([unit])\n\n-   unit: Time unit, the default value is [timer.unit](#timerunit)\n-   Returns: Timeline array.\n    -   key: Timeline key.\n    -   cost: Timeline cost.\n    -   unit: Time unit.\n    -   stoped: Whether the timeline is stopped.\n","scripts":{"build":"rm -rf lib && ../../node_modules/.bin/tsc","prepublish":"npm run build","test":"ROUTE_IP=10.227.30.24 RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=boe ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node"},"types":"lib/index.d.ts","version":"1.0.4-alpha.0","author":"","dependencies":{"@byted-service/reusify":"^1.0.2","tslib":"^1.9.3"},"description":"[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/timer.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.b